    • Constructor Detail

      • Builder

        public Builder(Context context)
        Initialize a bulider with a given context.

        This context will then be passed through to the rest of the Mesosfer SDK for use during initialization.

        You may define com.mesosfer.SERVER_URL, com.mesosfer.APPLICATION_ID and (optional) com.mesosfer.CLIENT_KEY meta-data in your AndroidManifest.xml: 

         <manifest ...>

 ...

   <application ...>
     <meta-data
       android:name="com.mesosfer.SERVER_URL"
       android:value="@string/Mesosfer_server_url" />
     <meta-data
       android:name="com.mesosfer.APPLICATION_ID"
       android:value="@string/Mesosfer_app_id" />
     <meta-data
       android:name="com.mesosfer.CLIENT_KEY"
       android:value="@string/Mesosfer_client_key" />

       ...

   </application>
 </manifest>

        This will cause the values for server, applicationId and clientKey to be set to those defined in your manifest.

        Parameters:
        context - The active Context for your application. Cannot be null.

        public Mesosfer.Configuration.Builder applicationId(String applicationId)
        Set the application id to be used by Mesosfer.

        This method is only required if you intend to use a different applicationId than is defined by com.mesosfer.APPLICATION_ID in your AndroidManifest.xml.

        Parameters:
        applicationId - The application id to set.
        Returns:
        The same builder, for easy chaining.
